<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE root [
<!ENTITY nbsp "&#160;">
]>
<html xmlns:frx="urn:FrxReports">
<head>
<title>Parameters</title>
<frx:category>Help</frx:category>
<frx:options hidden="1" />
<frx:fields>
  <frx:field id="title" link="reports/{name}"></frx:field>
</frx:fields>
<frx:parameters />
<frx:docgen />
</head>
<body>
  <div id="design_topics_block" frx:block="forena_help/design_topics">
    <h2
      style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 2px; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 1.429em; line-height: 1.4; color: #3b3b3b; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">
      <span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">Parmaters
        user provided inputs to a report. &nbsp;The following describes
        how parameter attributes are used by Forena.&nbsp;</span>
    </h2>
    <table border="0">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" align="left">id</th>
          <td><p>The unique id for the report paramter.
              &nbsp;Generally these must match exactly the parameters
              expected by the data values.&nbsp;</p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" align="left">label</th>
          <td><p>The label displayed to the user when prompted
              in the parameters form.&nbsp;</p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" align="left">default value</th>
          <td><p>Value to be used when none is specified.&nbsp;</p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" align="left">description</th>
          <td><p>Tell the users about what the parameter is
              used for as well as proper formats for entry.&nbsp;</p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" align="left">data source</th>
          <td><p>Used in conjuction with the control field to
              determine which values will be made available to raidios,
              checkboxes or select lists. &nbsp;The value should be a
              data block that users of this report will have access to.
              Blocks should be written to return key value pairs for use
              in these controls.&nbsp;</p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" align="left">data field</th>
          <td><p>Thefield that indicates which lookup values will be used to
                populate the return values of the select or radio buttons when a data source is specified.
            </p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" align="left">label field</th>
          <td><p>
              The field that indicates which lookup labels will be used to
              populate the labels of select or radio buttons when a data source is specified.
            </p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" align="left">Control</th>
          <td><p>
              <span
                style="color: #3b3b3b; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">Indicates
                the type of control or widget used prompt for user
                input.&nbsp;</span>
            </p>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Parameters can be removed by checking the remove box and
      saving the report.&nbsp;</p>
    <ul>
      <li id="forena_design_topics" frx:foreach="*">{title}</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
